title: For Sale:  M-31 Suomi
postcontent: This Finnish firearm was used to fight off Soviet Forces during the winter war of 1940 and showed the world the importance of sub-machine guns to modern warfare. Used by mostly Finnish and Swedish armies, it was also widely exported into Baltic countries, some European and South American countries. Although manufacturing of the Suomi in Finland ceased in 1944, it was widely used throughout the world well into the 1990’s. This Suomi M31 has been converted by TNW Firearms to Semi-Automatic and fires standard 9mm Luger / Parabellum rounds from a 36 round stick magazine or a 71 round drum. This carbine is discontinued and no more will be made, so it may go up in value. Accessories and magazines are plentiful. The barrel is removable. To convert to SA legal, TNW extended the barrel and converted it from open bolt to closed bolt with a redesigned bolt assembly. title: For Sale:  Bushnell 3-9x32 & Tasco 6x40 For Sale
location: Winston-Salem/Near WFU, Winston Salem, North Carolina
postcontent:
Two inexpensive scopes for sale—both have only been mounted on .22s.  My hunting .22s now all wear fixed 4X scopes or peep sights, so I don't have any more use for these.  They're both centerfire scopes, so they'd be a great option for adding inexpensive optics to a deer rifle, slug gun, etc.
The Bushnell is in good working condition but has some areas of surface wear from use (like the windage turret cap).  It held zero well and has finger-adjustable turrets.  The reticle is a medium duplex style.  It's a basic workhorse scope with a matte finish.
The Tasco is an older fixed 6x40 with a duplex reticle.  It's in very good condition and has coin/screwdriver adjustable turrets.  I used to live near a range that held rimfire benchrest competitions, and this fixed 6X allowed me to compete try out "hunter" class for far less money than a Weaver T6 or similar.  It held zero well and I never really had parallax issues from 50m on out.  However, there aren't any benchrest competitions in the Triad, and I prefer hunting with a 4X.  This is a simple scope that gives you just a bit more magnification than a 4X, and it has a gloss finish. 
I'm asking $20/ea or $35 for both.  Face-to-face sales in Winston-Salem only, please.
Armslist only lets me upload one photo, so email me and I can send pictures of the individual scopes, their turrets, lenses, and POV views of the reticles.
